  "text": "where v t follows uniform distribution on {1, 2, ..., n}. Stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and its variance reduced variants including SVRG have been shown to be powerful tools for solving the ERM problem, when n is large and computing the full gradient is computationally intensive. However, most of these algorithms implicitly assume that the gradient of each member function f i (\u00b7), i = 1, . . . , n is easy to obtain. However, this assumption fails to hold in the stochastic composition optimization problems [CITATION_1] ",
